org.processmining.plugins.interactivevisualization

Interface InteractiveVisualization


  • public interface InteractiveVisualization
    Interface for the Interactive Visualization The interactive visualization can provide a collection of events that are currently visible and a collection of events that have been selected by the user. It also keeps a reference to the most recent InteractivityManager instance. This manager can be used for further access to tags and instances.
    Author:
    Danny van Heumen

      • updateVisualization

        void updateVisualization(boolean logChanged,
                       boolean tagsChanged)
        Trigger an update (repaint) of the visualization. (e.g. because a tag has been updated.)
        Parameters:
        logChanged - Indicates that the log has been changed (e.g. filtered).
        tagsChanged - Indicates that one or more tags have been changed.

      • setManager

        void setManager(InteractivityManager manager)
        Set the manager that manages the interactivity between visualizations.
        Parameters:
        manager - The instance of the Interactivity Manager that manages interaction between visualizations.

      • getManager

        InteractivityManager getManager()
        Get the current Interactivity Manager instance.
        Returns:
        Returns the interactivity manager.

      • getSelectedElements

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.SortedSet<EID>> getSelectedElements()
        Get the elements that are selected in this visualization. (Representation in a set of Event IDs, but the visualization may of course display completely different things as long as they can be mapped to events.)
        Returns:
        Returns a collection of instances that define a specific set of events.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - In the case where this operation is not supported by the plugin implementing the InteractiveVisualization interface, this exception will be thrown. (E.g. when the plugin does not provide any means of selecting elements.)

      • getVisibleElements

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.SortedSet<EID>> getVisibleElements()
        Get the elements that are visible in this visualization. (e.g., one may be zoomed in on a particular area, this set represents the elements visible at that moment.)
        Returns:
        Returns a collection of instances that define the visible set of events.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - In the case this operation is not supported by the plugin implementing the InteractiveVisualization interface, this exception will be thrown.
